  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "71e74130-5113-44ad-9ed6-4e3e02035770",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Two classes used to distinguish exact dynamic programming algorithms are:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Value Iteration**:\n",
    "   - Iteratively updates the value function for each state until convergence, focusing on finding the optimal value function.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Policy Iteration**:\n",
    "   - Alternates between policy evaluation (calculating the value of a given policy) and policy improvement (updating the policy based on the value function) until an optimal policy is found."
   ]
